        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Quietman</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 08-16-98 11:35 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I think the PEZ collectors of the world have already started to tire of these color variations. Or at least, they're tired of paying upwards of $15 apiece for them.</font>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">The evidence: The latest batch of color variations don't seem to be fetching very high prices on eBay. I just saw auctions for the lion and pink elephant, which were still bidding at around $11.00, MOC. (And that was after the auction had been going for almost 7 days.) By comparison, the original set of color varations seemed to sell pretty quickly at $25.00 apiece MOC.</font></p>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">This decline in interest from collectors is perfectly natural. When the first batch of holiday variations came out, I'm sure a lot of people--myself included--thought, "Wow, these could be gone in no time, I'd better buy some." But here we are, however many months later, and the original color variations are still readily available... and already there's another round of variations. I guess it's obvious, now, that these things won't fly off the shelves overnight.</font></p>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">And I'm sure that the dealers realize this. Note that SJGlew's web page hasn't been offering the new set of color variations for very long, but they're already offering the selling them at a discount -- 2 for $30 as an alternative to $20 apiece.</font></p>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I still want that black witch, but I think I'll wait till it's under $10.<br></font></p>
          </td>
        </tr>
